subSubSection.paragraph:
Distribution.

Terebellum terebellum

was first recorded from the early Miocene of Saipan and the Marianas and later in the Pliocene of 
India
. Currently, this taxon ranges from the Red Sea throughout the tropical Indo-Pacific, and is especially common throughout the Philippine and Micronesian archipelagos (
Jung & Abbott 1967
). It is possible that the distributional records for 

Terebellum terebellum

includes examples of all extant taxa. HO- LOCENE 

